UML:TaggedValue.value: Provides functionality for separating layout and design from the PHP code. The template system supports compiling the code into PHP code to speed up the execution and allows third party add-ons to be made. The template system can be used to generate HTML pages, text files and emails.

Allows existing scripts to be easily integrated into the template output e.g.
index.php: $w = new ezcTemplateScriptWidget( 'active_users.php' );
pagelayout.tpl: {display $w)
The result is that the script is included and all output is catched using output buffering.
These classes are part of the public interface.
The compiler is involved to find the compiled code, this dependency must be removed.
The expression composed as PHP structure: 5 + 10 * $a + 20
The expression composed as element objects: 5 + 10 * $a + 20
